    <element name="Environmental Preservation" type="Spell" source="Omeria" id="ID_DMDAVE_OMERIA_SPELL_ENVIRONMENTAL_PRESERVATION">
        <supports>Druid, Ranger, Spell Saving Throw</supports>
        <description>
            <p>You make an area within range magically secure from harmful weather, destructive forces, and other effects. The area is a cube that can be 100 feet on each side. The spell lasts for the duration or until you use an action to dismiss it.</p>
            <p class="indent">When you cast the spell, you decide what sort of security the spell provides, choosing any or all of the following properties.</p>
            <ul>
                <li> The creatures and plants within the area are protected against extreme unnatural shifts in weather or climate. For example, an arctic environment would become immune to the effects of extreme heat, or a tropical forest would become immune to the effects of extreme cold.</li>
                <li>The barrier of the warded area appears blurry or foggy, preventing vision (including darkvision) through it.</li>
                <li>Until the spell ends, any creature inside the warded area that tries to damage or harm the nonmagical plants or beasts inside the warded area must first make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed saving throw, the creature cannot harm the area for 24 hours.</li>
                <li> Plant creatures and beasts inside the warded area have advantage on saving throws.</li>
                <li>The area comes under the protection of a fey creature called nature’s defender. It manifests within the warded area in an unoccupied space that you can see. The creature remains until it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends. The creature is friendly toward you and your companions, but it is not controlled by you. Its only purpose is to protect the warded area.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="indent">Casting this spell on the same spot every day for 1 year makes this effect permanent.</p>
            <p class="indent"><strong><em>At Higher Levels.</em></strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th level or higher, you can increase the size of the cube by 100 feet for each slot level beyond 5th. Thus you could protect a cube that can be up to 200 feet on one side by using a spell slot of 6th level. </p>
        </description>
        <setters>
            <set name="keywords"></set>
            <set name="level">5</set>
            <set name="school">Abjuration</set>
            <set name="time">10 minutes</set>
            <set name="range">range mile</set>
            <set name="duration">24 hours</set>
            <set name="hasVerbalComponent">true</set>
            <set name="hasSomaticComponent">true</set>
            <set name="hasMaterialComponent">true</set>
            <set name="materialComponent">soil from the target location, a feather, a candle, and a vial containing water from a nearby source</set>
            <set name="isConcentration">false</set>
            <set name="isRitual">true</set>
        </setters>
    </element>
    <element name="Fiendform" type="Spell" source="Omeria" id="ID_DMDAVE_OMERIA_SPELL_FIENDFORM">
        <supports>Bard, Sorcerer, Warlock, Wizard</supports>
        <description>
            <p>This spell temporarily turns a willing creature into a fiend. Until the spell ends, the creature’s type becomes fiend. Until the spell ends, the target gains the following benefits:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Resistance to cold, fire, and lightning damage.</li>
                <li>Darkvision out to 120 feet.</li>
                <li>Telepathy out to 60 feet.</li>
                <li>Advantage on saving throws against spells and other magical effects.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="indent">When the spell ends, the target’s mind is damaged by the spell’s effects. The target must succeed on a DC 10 Wisdom saving throw, or gain one form of long-term madness.</p>
        </description>
        <setters>
            <set name="keywords"></set>
            <set name="level">5</set>
            <set name="school">Transmutation</set>
            <set name="time">1 action</set>
            <set name="range">60 feet</set>
            <set name="duration">Concentration up to 1 hour</set>
            <set name="hasVerbalComponent">true</set>
            <set name="hasSomaticComponent">true</set>
            <set name="hasMaterialComponent">true</set>
            <set name="materialComponent">a charred piece of cloth</set>
            <set name="isConcentration">true</set>
            <set name="isRitual">false</set>
        </setters>
    </element>
    <element name="Four Horsemen" type="Spell" source="Omeria" id="ID_DMDAVE_OMERIA_SPELL_FOUR_HORSEMEN">
        <supports>Warlock, Wizard</supports>
        <description>
            <p>You call forth the spirits of four powerful warriors mounted on spectral horses. The horsemen manifest in unoccupied spaces that you can see within range. These incorporeal creatures each use the spectral horseman stat block. A horseman disappears when it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends.</p>
            <p class="indent">Each horseman is an ally to you and your companions. In combat, the horsemen share your initiative count, but take their turn immediately after yours. They obey your verbal commands (no action required by you). If you don’t issue any, they take the Dodge action and use their move to avoid danger.</p>
        </description>
        <setters>
            <set name="keywords">summon</set>
            <set name="level">8</set>
            <set name="school">Conjuration</set>
            <set name="time">1 action</set>
            <set name="range">90 feet</set>
            <set name="duration">Concentration up to 1 hour</set>
            <set name="hasVerbalComponent">true</set>
            <set name="hasSomaticComponent">true</set>
